<kml>

<concept name=Screen>
<superconcept name=Military-Task>

<definition>

  A form of security operation that primarily provides early warning
  to the protected force
  
</definition>

<requiredslotlist>

  <slotdescription name=agent>
     the <conceptref name=Military-Unit> that is screening the
     <slot>object</slot>
  </slotdescription>

  <slotdescription name=object>
     the <conceptref name=Military-Unit> that is being protected by the 
     <slot>agent</slot> by this screening operation
  </slotdescription>
  
  <slotdescription name=base>
     the <conceptref name=Military-Unit> that is being screened by the 
     <slot>agent</slot>
  </slotdescription>

</requiredslotlist>

  <comment>
  The <slot>agent</slot> and the <slot>object</slot> have the same
  <slot>allegiance</slot>, and the <slot>base</slot> has a different 
  <slot>allegiance</slot>
  </comment>

<neighborlist>

  <neighbor name=Guard>
    Guard is also a security action.  Guard means to fix an enemy
    ground force before it can engage the main body.
  </neighbor>

</neighborlist>

</kml>


